# No Bloat Coding Standard — Korax Systems

## Before writing anything
Read the existing file you are about to change. Understand what is already there before editing anything. Do not duplicate logic that already exists. Do not introduce a pattern that contradicts the existing pattern in the same file.

Before reading multiple source files to understand the codebase, query `graphify-out/graph.json` first. The knowledge graph answers structural questions faster and more accurately than reading files one by one. Run `graphify update .` if the graph is more than one session old.

## HTML rules
- No inline styles — all values belong in css/styles.css as CSS custom properties.
- No duplicate IDs — IDs must be unique per page, always.
- No empty alt attributes on meaningful images — every image needs a descriptive, keyword-aware alt.
- No deprecated elements or attributes (no `<center>`, no `align=`, no `border=` on tables).
- Semantic elements only — use `<nav>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<footer>`, `<main>` correctly.
- Do not add a second `<h1>` — exactly one per page.
- Do not reintroduce a Cloudflare email-decode script block — Cloudflare is DNS-only for this domain and does not proxy or inject scripts.

## CSS rules
- Check css/styles.css for existing CSS custom properties before writing any colour, spacing, or typography value. Never hardcode hex values, px sizes, or font names directly in selectors — use variables.
- No `!important` unless overriding a third-party injected style with no other option.
- No nested selectors deeper than three levels.
- Watch for specificity conflicts between class-based selectors (`.section`) and element-based selectors — they silently cancel each other out, especially on padding and margin for sections.
- No vendor prefixes unless the spec requires them. Unused rules must be removed, not commented out.
- prefers-reduced-motion must be respected for every transition or animation added.

## JavaScript rules
- No `var` — use `const` or `let` only.
- No `console.log` in any code that will be pushed to main.
- No functions longer than 30 lines — split into smaller named functions.
- No nested if/else deeper than two levels — use early returns.
- No magic numbers — name constants at the top of the file.
- No DOM manipulation libraries — this is vanilla JS; use native APIs.
- No new `<script>` tags added to index.html without an explicit confirmed decision.

## General rules
- Do not change behaviour — cleanup and refactor means changing how the code is written, not what it does.
- Do not touch files outside the agreed scope of the current task.
- One concern per function, one job per selector.
- If a change requires more than one file to be updated, confirm scope with @project-manager before starting.

## After every task
- Update `handoff.md` in `.cursor/` — one entry, three fields: what was changed, what was not touched, what to do next.
- Run `graphify update .` to refresh the knowledge graph before ending the session.
